<br>
<br>
There are 5 different types of zones in Lost Dungeons... There are the Guk (Deepest Guk), Mir (Miragul's Menagerie), Mmc (Mistmoore Catacombs), Ruj (Rujarkian Hills), and Tak (Takish'Hiz) dungeons. Each of these dungeons have 6-8 maps. Each instance uses similar architecture except for the 2 Points of Interest (POIs) in the zone. The zone name for each instance is named after a POI in the zone.<br>
<br>
To get an adventure, you need to go to a Wayfarer Camp. The Wayfarer Camps are in EverFrost, ECommons, NRo, SRo, and Butcher). You can go between each camp by using the Magus NPC. Once you are there, you need to find 4+ person group where everyone is within a 5 level range. Once you have the group, the leader right clicks on the Adventure Recruiter and gets an adventure. Once you have an adventure, you go to the zone entrance specified by the Adventure Window. You have 30 minutes to enter the zone. Once you have entered the zone, you have 90 minutes to complete the task assigned to you. You can check item collection or NPC kill stats from the Adventure Window.<br>
<br>
Adventures have many different types. For assassination adventure, you need to kill a specific number of NPCs in order to spawn the boss. Once you have spawned the boss, a EmoteZone will appear. You then go kill the boss and win the adventure. For rescue quests... You go to wherever the NPC you are searching for is held and kill the NPCs there. You then lead the NPC back to the entrance. Item collection and NPC killing quests are the same. They require you to either collect X items or kill Y of a certain type of NPC to win. There are no bosses in non assassinationk dungeons except the minibosses which spawn randomly.<br>
<br>
As for raids, they are designed for 16-36 VexThal+ equipped players. To get a raid, the raid leader talks to the Raid Recruiter. After the raid leader has received a raid, the adventure proceeds normally. The only difference between a raid adventure and a normal adventure is that raid adventures have a longer time limit.<br>
<br>
As for the rewards part of the Adventures, you go back to the Wayfarer Camp. Once at the camp, you can either use the Adventure Points you recieved from the adventure to buy items off the Adventure Merchants or see if you have done enough adventures to hear a story from a storyline NPC.<br>
<br>
Finally, there is an adventure completed/failed tracking system built in to Lost Dungeons of Norrath. This system tracks how many adventures in each theme you won/loss and calculates your win %. If you have a high enough total on any of the statistics, you get your character name placed on the Server Leaderboard. The Server Leaderboard is available for Total wins/losses/% and wins/losses/% for a specific theme.<br>
